node.text:
🪴 E𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕙 🪴 
Elemental magick forms a large part of my Craft so I thought I post some info about the elements and their correspondence. These items, like herbs and crystals are all things aligned with the element of Earth so can be incorporated in to spells or rituals to help you connect more with the ground beneath our feet. 

Left to right in the graphic represents: direction, the qualities of  Earth, zodiac signs, colours, crystals, herbs, physical items that can be used to symbolise Earth, planets.

Working with the elements is a great form of magick for those at the start of their Witchcraft journey. The beauty of this magick is in its simplicity. The elements can be represented by simple ingredients such as a glass of water (Water), soil/crystals (Earth), incense (Air) and a candle (Fire).

What element do you connect with the most?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨𝕆𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕝𝕖 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨
1. 𝕊𝕠𝕦𝕥𝕙 ℕ𝕠𝕕𝕖 ☋
The South Node reveals the challenges and gifts we bring in from previous lifetimes. It represents our fears and our insecurities. Have you been struggling to control your fears lately? You may even feel like your fears are controlling you. The South Node suggests these fears may be an overdeveloped character trait from your other lives that you find easy to fall back on (it’s familiar) but that may undermine your growth. The key to overcoming these fears is to embrace them - take on the things that bring you fear. You are more than strong enough, and once you start, you may realise you were worrying far too much. Don’t let your fears paralyse you

2. ℙ𝕒𝕝𝕝𝕒𝕤 𝔸𝕥𝕙𝕖𝕟𝕖 
Pallas Athene, an asteroid, can come as a flash of insight or sudden creative inspiration. Things may have been stressful recently, but you need to shift your perspective in order to understand what you need to do to move forward. This card represents your ability to connect with your intuition and higher self. Have you been ignoring your intuition lately? Connecting with your intuition will help you shift your perspective and you need to be open to what it’s telling you. You might feel you’ve lost touch and perspective with your goals, but this card is encouragement to get things back on track

3. 𝕃𝕒𝕤𝕥 ℚ𝕦𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕖𝕣 
This card represents the letting go of blockages so you are able to actively move toward in a positive direction. You may be feeling somehow stuck, but The Last Quarter brings in the transitional energy that makes moving forward possible. But to make this change, you must actively practice self forgiveness. Are you too hard on yourself? It’s time to be more loving and patient towards yourself as you are with others. Forgive yourself for the things that didn’t work out and free yourself from the limiting energy that comes along with not cutting yourself some slack. Making this adaption is crucial to help prepare you for the new things coming your way. It will help you navigate with ease any challenges and obstacles. 

#tarot #divination #healing #witch #witchcraft #witchy #witches #energy #witchythings #witchystuff

node.text:
As we get closer to the Autumn Equinox and Samhain, it got me looking at family photos. 

This photograph is one of four female generations of my family. My mum is the little girl, held by my great grandmother, and the lady sat down at the front is my great great grandmother Jane. I was given her name as my middle name. I’m so happy I have this photo of my ancestors. I love finding out more about my family.

Do you have any old photos of your ancestors that are special to you?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨ M𝕖𝕣𝕔𝕦𝕣𝕪 R𝕖𝕥𝕣𝕠𝕘𝕣𝕒𝕕𝕖 ✨
We entered the shadow period for Mercury retrograde yesterday, although retrograde doesn’t officially begin on 26 September.

The shadow period is where the effects of retrograde can be felt as we get closer to 26 September and the start of retrograde itself. 

These are some general tips for retrograde survival. The planet Mercury rules communication in all forms like listening, writing, reading, speaking. It also rules activities related to communication, like negotiations and contracts.

I must admit, I think Mercury Retrograde has an unfair reputation. It’s associated with chaos, bad communication, difficulties with technology and aggression with people losing their tempers. 

Of course, this could be the case sometimes, but some blame retrograde for all chaos that happens in their lives. Instead, look at Mercury Retrograde in a more positive light and all the opportunities it can bring.

Mercury presents you with a fantastic chance to sit back and reflect. Review what you put your energy toward and reanalyse who you are, what you’re doing and where you want to be.

What are your thoughts about Mercury Retrograde? ✨🪐

Lindsay 💜
————————————————————

node.text:
I want to say a massive thank you for all the beautiful messages you left me when I told you about Salem. They brought me a lot of comfort.

I wanted to share a picture of Salem’s final resting place. It’s a small altar in the living room so he can always be in the middle of family life. Although I know they are just earthy remains, I’m happier now he’s back at home where he belongs.

The feather is very special as it was the last one he ever brought me. Rather than bringing dead animals as gifts, Salem used to love to bring us leaves and feathers. 

Until we meet again my angel 💔

Lindsay 💜

✨T𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The Moon is a reminder not to take everything at face value. Sometimes we only know half a story and don’t have all the information you need to move forward. Listen to your intuition so you can see beyond what’s in front of you. Feel into situations rather thinking what they mean. Let go of negative self talk and allow your intuition to guide you and give you a greater level of understanding. Feel into situations rather than overthinking what they might mean. Pay attention to your dreams, they can also give you guidance about which direction to go. 

2. The Nine of Cups is often known as the wish card as it’s an excellent omen that the things you’re working towards will soon come to fruition. Keep using your intentions to work towards your goal. Remember that what you put into the Universe, you receive, so keep a positive approach and this energy will be returned to you through success and fulfilment. This card is also a reminder to count your blessings and be consciously grateful for the people in your life. Overtime, this will help to intensify feelings of contentment as well as your ability to attract what you wish for. You attract what you give.

3. The Two of Pentacles suggests you are currently juggling many different responsibilities and you’re struggling to manage them all together. There’s lots on your mind and this card asks you to manage your time and priorities carefully. It’s about trying to achieve some sort of balance so you can also get some down time. You may be losing sight of the bigger picture and instead you get lost and stressed out by the little details. You need to stop and step back for a while so you can explore and ask yourself what you actually want from life. Sometimes taking a break can be the most productive thing you can do so you can reassess your responsibilities and priorities.
